					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper. </support>
								<extent>313 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>152</height>
										<width>102</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>120</height>
										<width>80</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>313 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 6 leaves each. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Folios missing after folio 161, 173, 222.</p>
									<p>Slightly stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="17" writtenLines="17">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible ruling with a mastara.</p>
									<p>Initial words of each section written in larger characters, preceded with a title page (see e.g. folio 224r, 240r, etc).</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>The biblical verses are given with punctuation.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Square and semi-cursive Oriental script of the 17th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Avraham ben Mordekhai ha-Kohen</name>: inscribed, volume 2, folio 220v and volume 3, folio 126v. Avraham ha-Kohen wrote the present manuscript for his son, Yosef. The name of the latter is inscribed under the title of each Muḳadimah.</summary>
